Shares of Continental Gummi-Werke AG&lt;CONG.F> opened eight marks stronger in an otherwise mixedFrankfurt market and dealers attributed the trend to favourablepress reports about a new tyre system the company isdeveloping.    The shares later eased to 344.50.    A spokesman for the West German Automobile Association,ADAC, said the ADAC magazine in a recent edition describedadvantages of the new tyre. REUTER&#3;